    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "why would honey make it worse though? i read online that medical grade honey is actually used in hospitals for wound care because it kills bacteria. it seems like a lot of effort to go to the ER just for a cut that isnt even spraying blood or anything, it just wont stop leaking a little bit. can't i just clean it really well and use the honey to help it close up?",
